          "**Word documents** - Embed charts for reports",
          "**PowerPoint presentations** - Use in slides",
          "**PDF reports** - Include in formal reports",
          "**Web pages** - Export for web use",
          "**Print materials** - High-resolution output"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Presentation Tips"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**One chart per slide** - Focus attention",
          "**Clear titles** - Descriptive chart names",
          "**Speaker notes** - Explain chart meaning",
          "**Animation** - Reveal data progressively",
          "**Handouts** - Provide detailed information"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Best Practices Summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "**Plan first** - Define purpose and audience",
          "**Choose data** - Select relevant information",
          "**Select chart type** - Match data characteristics",
          "**Create chart** - Use Excel's chart tools",
          "**Customize** - Apply formatting and styling",
          "**Review** - Check accuracy and clarity",
          "**Refine** - Make improvements",
          "**Share** - Distribute to stakeholders"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "content": "Always test your charts with your intended audience. What makes sense to you might not be clear to others. Get feedback and refine your visualizations accordingly."
    }
  ]
